HEADWORD: Likable
<hw>Lik"a*ble</hw> <pr>(l⟦imac⟧k"⟦adot⟧*b'l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<def>Such as can be liked; such as to attract liking; easy to like;
evoking sympathy; <as>as, a <ex>likable</ex> person</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Thackeray.</au></rj> <wns>[wns=1+2]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> appealing, likable.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>disposed to please.</def> <wns>[wns=3]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> amiable, agreeable, good-humored, good-humoured,
likable.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

